sap.m.MessageBox.description:
Provides easier methods to create sap.m.Dialog with type sap.m.DialogType.Message, such as standard alerts, confirmation dialogs, or arbitrary message dialogs.

As <code>MessageBox</code> is a static class, a <code>jQuery.sap.require("sap.m.MessageBox");</code> statement must be explicitly executed before the class can be used. Example: <pre>
  jQuery.sap.require("sap.m.MessageBox");
  sap.m.MessageBox.show(
      "This message should appear in the message box.", {
          icon: sap.m.MessageBox.Icon.INFORMATION,
          title: "My message box title",
          actions: [sap.m.MessageBox.Action.YES, sap.m.MessageBox.Action.NO],
          onClose: function(oAction) { / * do something * / }
      }
    );
</pre>

